VAural treat for music lovers
p3
sVnews
p4
VSYED MUTHAHAR SAQAFThe Sri Rama Gana Sabha Trust recently conducted its annual music and dance festival at  Bala Kala Vidhanam auditorium,  Renga Nagar, Tiruchi, for two days.T. V. Ramprasadh presented a vocal concert on the first day. He was accompanied by artistes from All India Radio, Tiruchi,  T.V. Ramanujacharlu (violin) and B. Harikumar (mridangam).Excellent explorationRamprasadh commenced the concert with the ``Jalajakshi'' (Hamsadhwani) varnam. His excellent exploration of Todi for about an hour in Todi kept the audience in rapt attention. It was followed by ``Kadaikkan Parayo'' of Papanasam Sivan in Begada, set to misra chapu talam.The next day, flute maestro, N. Ramani delighted the audience.N. C. Madhav rendered able support on the violin, Valangaiman Thyagarajan on the mridangam and Malaikottai Deenadayalu on the morsing.Ramani set off with the Sriragam varnam, followed by a kirtana of Saint Tyagaraja, "Vinayaka Ninu" in Hamsadhwani. His excellent delineation of Kharaharapriya followed by a rendition of ``Chakaniraja,''  lasted for about 45 minutes.  ``Akilandeswari" of Muthuswami Dikshitar, followed by "Baro Krishnayya" (ragamalika) added lustre to the recital.The music festival was inaugurated by the Chief General Manager, Chettinad Cements, C. Sudhakar, in the presence of Whole Time Director, Dalmia (Bharat) Cement, N. Gopalaswami.Bottom Template Starts
